abstract: State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
snippet: State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — State attorneys general investigating Alphabet Inc's Google unit met on Tuesday with U.S. Justice Department officials to coordinate efforts to probe the search and advertising giant, officials told Reuters.
headline_main: State AGs, Justice Department Discuss Google Antitrust Probe
headline_print_headline: State AGs, Justice Department Discuss Google Antitrust Probe

abstract: The Trump administration plans to meet this month to discuss further curbing technology exports to China and its flagship telecoms company Huawei, two sources said, in a bid to resolve differences within the government over the possible crackdown.
snippet: The Trump administration plans to meet this month to discuss further curbing technology exports to China and its flagship telecoms company Huawei, two sources said, in a bid to resolve differences within the government over the possible crackdown.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration plans to meet this month to discuss further curbing technology exports to China and its flagship telecoms company Huawei, two sources said, in a bid to resolve differences within the government over the possible crackdown.
headline_main: U.S. to Review New Curbs on Huawei, China in Feb. Meeting: Sources
headline_print_headline: U.S. to Review New Curbs on Huawei, China in Feb. Meeting: Sources

abstract: CONCORD, N.H. — Day 2 of the weeklong sprint to the New Hampshire primary began early Wednesday as several of the Democratic presidential candidates, including Pete Buttigieg and Senator Amy Klobuchar, discussed climate change and clean energy at a daylong forum here.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Day 2 of the weeklong sprint to the New Hampshire primary began early Wednesday as several of the Democratic presidential candidates, including Pete Buttigieg and Senator Amy Klobuchar, discussed climate change and clean energy at a daylong forum here.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg held a slight lead over Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the Democratic race for the presidential nomination, according to partial results released by the Iowa Democratic Party.
headline_main: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders
headline_print_headline: Partial Iowa Results Give Buttigieg Slight Edge Over Sanders

abstract: Venezuelan opposition leader Juan Guaidó on Wednesday scored a long-sought meeting with President Donald Trump, a high point on an international tour aimed at bolstering support for Guaidó's U.S.-backed campaign to oust President Nicolas Maduro.
snippet: Venezuelan opposition leader Juan Guaidó on Wednesday scored a long-sought meeting with President Donald Trump, a high point on an international tour aimed at bolstering support for Guaidó's U.S.-backed campaign to oust President Nicolas Maduro.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Venezuelan opposition leader Juan Guaidó on Wednesday scored a long-sought meeting with President Donald Trump, a high point on an international tour aimed at bolstering support for Guaidó's U.S.-backed campaign to oust President Nicolas Maduro.
headline_main: Venezuelan Opposition Head Meets Trump in Show of US Support
headline_print_headline: Venezuelan Opposition Head Meets Trump in Show of US Support

abstract: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
snippet: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
lead_paragraph: The Senate acquitted President Trump on Wednesday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress, as Republicans turned back an election-year attempt by House Democrats to remove him from office for pressuring a foreign power to incriminate his political rivals.

abstract: Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar will leave New Hampshire and zip back to Washington today for the final moments of President Trump’s impeachment trial.
lead_paragraph: Senators Bernie Sanders, Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar will leave New Hampshire and zip back to Washington today for the final moments of President Trump’s impeachment trial.
headline_main: Senators skipped Trump’s speech, but they’ll vote to convict him.

abstract: The Iraqi government has told its military not to seek assistance from the U.S.-led coalition in operations against the Islamic State group, two senior Iraqi military officials said, amid a crisis of mistrust between Washington and Baghdad after an American strike killed a top Iranian general and an Iraqi militia commander.
snippet: The Iraqi government has told its military not to seek assistance from the U.S.-led coalition in operations against the Islamic State group, two senior Iraqi military officials said, amid a crisis of mistrust between Washington and Baghdad after a...
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — The Iraqi government has told its military not to seek assistance from the U.S.-led coalition in operations against the Islamic State group, two senior Iraqi military officials said, amid a crisis of mistrust between Washington and Baghdad after an American strike killed a top Iranian general and an Iraqi militia commander.
headline_main: Iraqi Officials Say Baghdad Wants to Minimize Reliance on US
headline_print_headline: Iraqi Officials Say Baghdad Wants to Minimize Reliance on US
